Singer 2Baba’s wife, Annie Idibia, has opened up on the hurt she feels over the reality that her first child with her husband is his fifth. The actress revealed this in a chat with her co-stars on the “Young, Famous and African” reality show where she also explained the numerous humiliations and embarrassments that have caused her. She said it was more painful because he met her husband before the other persons who he shares kids with. The mother of two said: “When you meet someone, then you know them first and then you wake up to different people are having babies for him.   Bianca/Ebele faceoff disgraceful to womanhood – MASSOB     Putin complains of Ukrainian ‘war crimes’ in phone call with…     Police denies shooting at a Corps member in Ibadan   “And then he has five different kids with other women. And my first child is his fifth and I met him before everybody. So you know what that is. “You know how many humiliations and embarrassment? Damn! And I was like… man…how do you repeat the same mistake twice? It’s all pain, it hurts. The reality star, however, noted as a couple, they have forever to make up for all the awful moments they’ve had in the past. “But like I always say, the good times are so much more. And I have forever with him to make up for the bad times”, she added.